snippet.textDisplay:
"...to say things like "Our house is on fire", or "I wanted to panic.", or "How dare you?". But today I will not do that. Because then, those phrases are all that people focus on.
They don't remember the facts; the very reason I say those things in the first place.
We now no longer have time to leave out the science.
Without seeing the full picture, we will not solve this crisis.
Finding wholistic solutions, is what The Cop25 should be all about."

- Greta Thunberg. (The Cop25 climate talks)

Greta, you are a divise liar on too many levels.
How dare you accuse us of not remembering the facts.
How dare you accuse us of leaving out the science.
How dare you accuse us of not seeing the big picture.
How dare you accuse us of "only focusing" on your nonsense appeals to emotion.

We are focusing on the facts, the actual science, and the bigger picture.

We are not the side claiming science by consensus, nor are we claiming that the science is settled. Those are the claims of science deniers. You are the science denier.

We are seeing the bigger picture, as we have seen a decades long history of climate catastrophists such as the "scientific" claims you propose as getting it so wrong, it defies being accidental.

We do know the facts.
We know that more government, and more taxation is far from any solution to anything.
We know that plant food is not a poison.
We know about the Earth's cycles.
We know that the false prognostications of the religion of Envirofacism are almost entirely wrong, and have only ever been wrong.

We're not denying science,
We're not denying that there are problems.
We're not denying anything you're falsely, and dishonestly accusing us of.

You are typical of the myopic Left, that isolates out all the factors of any issue, then seeks to polarise people over it.
That divisiveness has to stop.
Even if you are correct, this behaviour is destroying your own purpose.
Your words are a deep insult to those who are intelligent enough to know that claims of consensus science, and that the science is settled, are more than enough reason to be sceptical.
And you're wanting to solve this "crisis" that is yet to show itself as the crisis you claim it to be, by demanding others do the changing is disgusting.

Greta.
Stop lying.

How dare you.

In Sub-Saharan Africa 35% of the population experienced malnutrition
in 1991. In 2015 that rate was down to 17%. Crop yields have increased
exponentially since this recent rise in atmospheric CO2 levels. Corn yields in
1940 in the US were 2 tonnes per hectare. In 2014 the yield was 10
tonnes per hectare. World illiteracy has decreased from 90% in 1800 to 12%

decrease over 80 years. Life expectancy has risen from age 40 in
1900 to about 70 now. According to a study on frequency and cost

It is a scientific fact that Co2 emissions are heavier than air and therefore disperse all around us. Such emissions do not rise up into the stratosphere.

Although methane, from humans, from cows and Co gas (carbon monoxide), are potential greenhouse gases, their effect is relatively short-lived. So perhaps the climate change and the global warming that spelled the end of the recognised Ice-Age, over 12,000 years ago, is also what is happening now?
